DAY 1 REVIEW:
HTML: 
-MarkUp Language
-Use html tags to create elements
    -h1-h6 -> header
    -p -> paragraph
    -Opening tag : <h1>
    -Closing tag : </h1>
    -Example : <h1> How are you? </h1>
-CSS:
-Cascading Style Sheet
-Used for adding style such as color, width, height, spacings,...
-3 ways to use CSS
    -1. Inline :  <h1 style="color: red"> How are you? </h1>
    -2. Internal : Use style in HTML file 
    <style> 
        h1{
            color:red
        }
    </style>
    -3. External : Create an external CSS Sheet.
    In styles.css, we can use css files without using <style> keyword
        h1{
            color:red
        }
NOTE:
1. external styling is prefered since it makes the code clean
2. We should not use tags for styling. class is the most common way for styling
-Class is used for styling MULTIPLE ELEMENTS. Class can repeat. . = class
-Id is used for styling UNIQUE ELEMENTS. Id should not repeat. # = id
